         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">28/4/67 ¶  ¶ In my letters, posted this morning, dear Dr Hooker, I omitted to mention, that should poor Harveys widow in any way be interested in the monetary proceeds of the phycologia, let then, pra...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">67.04.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, f. 267.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">28/4/67</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In my letters, posted this morning, dear Dr Hooker, I omitted to mention, that should poor Harveys widow in any way be interested in the monetary proceeds of the phycologia, let then, pray, at once the sum I am still charged be paid in full, otherwise please use your own discretion.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The reference is to the sale of copies of Harvey (1858-63) sent to M; see M to J. Hooker, 25 October 1866.</p>
               </note> I ought perhaps to be more liberal, but really after 20 years stay in Australia I am finally almost worse off than when I came &amp; must thus husband my slender resources, otherwise I shall never be able to establish a domestic home.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I send you some paper samples. Should you have received them already from Government direct, pray give these small bits to some other phytologic Museum.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Fifteen samples of paper were entered in the Museum entry book Kew, 1861-79, p. 181, on 1 July 1867.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have commenced a tabellar<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">tabular?</p>
               </note> statistic of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">all</hi>
               </seg> plants of Australia, in which medicinal, technological, geographical &amp;c indications are given. I shall complete it as a byework.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M appears never to have published the tabulation.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Could not Prof Balfour send you a small off-shoot of Mesembryanthemum tegens. It reached Edinburgh quite safely.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Balfour, 27 December 1866 (in this edition as 66-12-27a).</p>
               </note> Should "<name key="Enhydra">Enhydra</name>" not be changed to <name key="Meyera">Meyera</name> or <name key="Sobreyra">Sobreyra</name> as it is also a zoologic name!<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">One of four genera of the weasel family (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Mustelidae</seg>). <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Enhydra">Enhydra</name> lutris</seg> is the sea otter.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Enhydra">Enhydra</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Mesembryanthemum%20tegens%20">Mesembryanthemum tegens </name>
            </p>
